The **expense ratio** is the annual fee deducted from a mutual fund's NAV to cover management, administrative, and distribution costs. While 0.5–2% sounds small, compounded over decades, even a 1% higher expense ratio can reduce your final corpus by 15–30%. This calculator shows the exact impact on your wealth.
